Five workers were attacked by a swarm of bees, leaving one in a critical condition, in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday. IPSS Medical Rescue said  the workers were cleaning a roof in KwaDukuza on the north coast. “One patient is in a critical condition and is being stabilised by IPSS Advanced Life Support paramedics and will be flown via helicopter to a specialised facility. “Three  workers  escaped with minor reactions. They were treated at the scene. They did not require transport to hospital.” TimesLIVE